main event: A series of radar images and diagrams from Whiteman AFB in Missouri, dated November 6, 1957, appear to show the tracking of an unidentified flying object (UFO).
interesting points: The radar images and diagrams contain technical labels and details such as 'ELEVATION SCOPE', 'AZIMUTH SCOPE', 'RUNWAY CENTER LINE', and 'PERMANENT TARGET'.
The radar images show a circular target or 'blip' labeled as a 'UFOB' (Unidentified Flying Object).
The dates on the images range from 1834L on November 6, 1957 to 1954L on November 6, 1957, indicating the object was tracked over an extended period.
The radar images appear to show the UFO maneuvering, with one image labeling the object as being on the 'RUNWAY CENTER LINE'.
The report is designated as 'File 5178' and indicates it is part of the Project Blue Book investigations into UFO sightings.
sighted object: unidentified flying object (UFO) tracked on radar
photographs: yes, the report includes radar tracking images and diagrams
